Before jenkins Install Java, it is a prerequisite.
java -version


Refer documentation -
https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/linux/


TO INCLUDE THE JAVA INSTALLED DIRECTORY IN THE DEFAULT PATH VARIABLE WHERE ALL THE DIRECTORIES OF EXECUTABLE FILES ARE PRESENT 
export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-11-openjdk-amd64
export PATH=$PATH:$JAVA_HOME/bin
echo $PATH
This is to tell jenkins where the JAVA is present so that it can run Java commands.This path of JAVA_HOME is used in the "manage jenkins->tools" section in the jenkins console.
